==English==
===Noun===
'''gaff''' (''plural'' ''gaffs'')

#{{cattag|fishing}} A [[tool]] consisting of a large metal [[hook]] with a handle or pole, used to pull in large [[fish]].
#(''British slang'') A place of residence.
#:''We're going round to Mike's gaff later to watch the footie.''
#{{cattag|nautical}} The upper [[spar]] used to control a gaff-rigged [[sail]].

